ownedElements.name: Date
ownedElements.documentation: Date without time component. Examples: Effective Date, Order Date.

ownedElements.name: Timestamp
ownedElements.documentation: Combined date and time component. Examples: Approval Timestamp, Begin Cook Timestamp.

ownedElements.name: Identifier
ownedElements.documentation:
Synonymous with the "Number" Attribute Class.
Business identifier for an entity. Note that this class is not synonymous with a database ID column that is not typically visible to business users. Examples: Customer Number, Order Number, Employee Number.

ownedElements.name: Number
ownedElements.documentation:
Synonymous with the "Identifier" Attribute Class.
Business identifier for an entity. Note that this class is not synonymous with a database ID column that is not typically visible to business users. Examples: Customer Number, Order Number, Employee Number.

ownedElements.name: Ordinal
ownedElements.documentation: Integer value indicating an ordinal position. Examples: Sort Index, Order Line Number.

ownedElements.name: Locator
ownedElements.documentation: Identifies a location or address of contact. For example: Address LIne 1, Memory Address, Email Address, Lattitude, Longitude.

ownedElements.name: Code
ownedElements.documentation: Abbreviated reference for an entity, typically without whitespace or case sensitivity.

ownedElements.name: Name
ownedElements.documentation: Formal, legal or official reference to an entity or organization. Examples: State Name, Company Name, Employee Name, Customer Name.

ownedElements.name: Description
ownedElements.documentation: Describes an entity, but does not quality as a Name or Code. Examples: Billing Status Description, Return Reason Description.

ownedElements.name: Note
ownedElements.documentation: Text that does not otherwise classify as a Name, Code, or Description. Examples: Comment, Notes.

ownedElements.name: Flag
ownedElements.documentation: Indicates Yes/No or True/False values. Flag is not used to represent enumerated values; these should be created as enumerations or as a separate entity. Examples: Order Fulfilled Flag, Employed Flag, Completed Flag.

ownedElements.name: List
ownedElements.documentation: Indicates that the attribute represents a list of values. Ideally, this type of attribute would be represented as a separate entity. Examples: Tag List, Email List.

ownedElements.name: Currency
ownedElements.documentation: Numeric value that has units of currency. Best practice is to accompany with a Currency attribute or prefix the attribute with a Currency Code. Examples: Sales Amount, Cost Amount, USD Cost Amount.

ownedElements.name: Value
ownedElements.documentation: Numeric value that does not otherwise qualify as Currency, Rate or Quantity. Examples: NPS Score.

ownedElements.name: Value Integer
ownedElements.documentation:
Special case of the "Value" Attribute Class where the value is an Integer.
Numeric value that does not otherwise qualify as Currency, Rate or Quantity. Examples: Year.

ownedElements.name: Quantity
ownedElements.documentation: Numeric value used to quantify a number of units. Best practice is to accompany with a Unit of Measure attribute. Examples: Order Case Quantity.

ownedElements.name: Rate
ownedElements.documentation: Fractional value without units frequently falling between 0.0 and 1.0. Used to represent attributes that may be formatted as percentage. Examples: Gross Margin Rate, Completion Rate.

ownedElements.name: Count
ownedElements.documentation: Value indicating the number of items in a set. Examples: Employee Count, Order Count.

ownedElements.name: Indicator
ownedElements.documentation: Represents a binary value such as True/False, Yes/No, 0/1. Examples: Active, Closed.
